-- PepsiCo to build $170 mln Russia snack plant
-- 
-- Sat Jun 9, 2007 9:11am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/09/us-russia-forum-pepsi-idUSL0946727120070609

 

 ST PETERSBURG, Russia  (Reuters) - PepsiCo International ( PEP.N ) said on Saturday it would build a snacks production plant in the Russian town of Azov and invest $170 million over five years in the project. 

 The project, which would create 1,000 jobs, is PepsiCo's second major manufacturing investment in Russia, where it already operates a $160 million plant in Kashira, near Moscow.